{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ad4a4693-b40f-4572-8fce-5375e96755f7","content":"Your project isn't in the workspace, but here's the `mcp.json` configuration you need. Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`command`/`args`** — uses `dotnet run` to build and launch your server.\n- Your MCP server must use **stdio transport** (not HTTP/SSE). If using the `ModelContextProtocol` NuGet package, that means calling `.WithStdioServerTransport()`.\n\nAfter saving, open the Copilot chat in agent mode (`@`), and it will discover your server's tools automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ae7f8c57-7ca7-4694-aeca-9af766b583af","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist yet, but the user said they built it. They're just asking for configuration guidance. I'll provide the mcp.json configuration they need.","outputTokens":299,"requestId":"3C0A:787A3:1C6025:21D55A:69E81D07"},"id":"406213d1-aa95-476c-a968-015bf5bd9d91","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:57:58.053Z","parentId":"55ce8074-5df8-4857-a456-22f5cbbe9457"}
